<!-- COMMS PROTOCOL — READ FIRST -->

This repo uses `comms` (github.com/dpa-plus/comms) for multi-agent coordination.

**On every session start, before any other work:**
```bash
comms hello && comms status
```

**Before any file edit:**
```bash
comms claim "src/path/to/file.ts" --intent "what you're changing"
```
If exit code 1: read stderr, surface the conflict to the user, ask whether the prior session is alive. If user authorizes, use `--steal <id> --reason "..."`.

**When done with a claim:**
```bash
comms release --result "PR #123 merged"
```

**Record findings:**
```bash
comms find fix "..." --ref path:src/foo.ts --ref commit:abc1234     # problem resolved
comms find bug "..." --ref path:src/bar.ts                          # open problem
comms find decision "..." --ref doc:slug                            # architecture choice
comms find gotcha "..." --ref path:src/auth.ts                      # persistent trap
comms find ship "..." --ref pr:#123                                 # released
```

**FAILURE TO RUN `comms hello` BEFORE FIRST EDIT IS A PROTOCOL VIOLATION.**

<!-- END COMMS PROTOCOL -->
